.TH SIMPLE_SHELL 1 "April 2025" "Educational Project"
.SH NAME
simple_shell \- UNIX command interpreter implementation
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ./hsh
.SH OVERVIEW
.B simple_shell
is an educational implementation of a UNIX shell designed to demonstrate process creation, command parsing, and environment management principles.
.SH OPERATIONAL CHARACTERISTICS
.SS Interactive Mode
.RS
.IP \(bu 3
Displays prompt: ($)
.IP \(bu 3
Reads commands from standard input
.IP \(bu 3
Executes commands and displays results
.RE
.SS Non-interactive Mode
.RS
.IP \(bu 3
Reads commands from standard input or files
.IP \(bu 3
Executes without user interaction
.IP \(bu 3
Suitable for scripting and automation
.RE
.SH BUILT-IN DIRECTIVES
.TP
.B exit
Terminates shell execution
.TP
.B env
Outputs environment variable definitions
.SH PATH RESOLUTION
Utilizes PATH environment variable for command location. Supports both absolute and relative path specifications.
.SH CUSTOM SCRIPTS
Compatible with executable scripts including demonstration script:
.TP
.B /home/student_jail/student_repo/hbtn_ls
.SH DEVELOPMENT
.RS
